  "prompt_text": "Describe the bittersweet feeling of watching your best friend get married when you're single.",
  "response_text": "Watching your best friend get married can be a bittersweet experience, especially if you're single. On one hand, you're overjoyed for your friend, who has found someone they love and are committing to for the rest of their life. You're happy to see them happy, and you can't help but feel a sense of pride and excitement for the new chapter they're about to embark on. You've shared countless memories with this person, and the thought of them starting a new life with their partner is a beautiful thing.\n\nHowever, as you watch them exchange their vows and promise to love and cherish each other, you can't help but feel a pang of sadness. You're reminded that you're still single, and that you're not at the same stage in your life. You might feel a sense of nostalgia for the carefree days of your friendship, when it was just the two of you, and you didn't have to worry about anyone else's needs or expectations.\n\nYou might also feel a twinge of jealousy, wondering when it's your turn to find someone special. You might start to question whether you'll ever find someone who loves and accepts you for who you are, or if you'll be stuck in a state of singledom forever. These feelings can be overwhelming, especially if you're someone who values close relationships and feels like you're missing out on the experience of being in a committed partnership.\n\nBut as you watch your friend's wedding, you're also reminded of the importance of friendship and the love and support that you share with each other. You know that your friendship is strong and unbreakable, and that you'll continue to be there for each other through thick and thin. You might even find yourself feeling grateful for the opportunity to be a part of your friend's special day, and to celebrate their love and commitment to each other.\n\nUltimately, watching your best friend get married can be a bittersweet experience, but it's also a reminder of the beauty and power of love and friendship. It's 